// =============================================================================
// adx_seed.kql — synthetic data seeding for the detection-diary KQL tests
// Author:    Jarmi
// Date:      2026-05-08
// Purpose:   Populate the schema created by adx_bootstrap.kql with handcrafted
//            positive and negative rows for every KQL rule in days/*/kql/.
// Usage:
//   1. Bootstrap must already be done. Confirm with `.show tables` (15 tables).
//   2. Paste this whole file in the ADX query window.
//   3. Click anywhere INSIDE the `.execute database script <|` block and Run.
//   4. Verify with `DeviceFileEvents | count` — must return 14.
//
// Why this shape:
//   ADX rejects multiple `.ingest` commands in one query (recognition error).
//   `.execute database script <|` batches them into a single server-side run.
//   The body must contain control commands flush-left and free of `//` comments.
//
// Convention:
//   DeviceId  = d-<dayN>-<seq>     (filterable per rule)
//   Hostnames = WIN-<dayN>-<seq>   for Windows / WIN11
//               LIN-<dayN>-<seq>   for Linux
//   Timestamps within last 6 days (rules use `ago(7d)` filter).
// =============================================================================

.execute database script <|
.clear table DeviceFileEvents data
.clear table DeviceProcessEvents data
.clear table DeviceNetworkEvents data
.clear table DeviceLogonEvents data
.clear table SecurityEvent data
.clear table Syslog data
.clear table AuditLogs data
.clear table SigninLogs data
.clear table CloudAppEvents data
.clear table OfficeActivity data
.clear table EmailUrlInfo data
.clear table EmailAttachmentInfo data
.clear table GitHubAuditLogs data
.ingest inline into table DeviceNetworkEvents <|
